The Vice President of the United States, along with other government officials, gathered at Arlington National Cemetery to honor and thank veterans on Veterans Day. The Vice President expressed gratitude for the sacrifices made by service members and their families. She emphasized the importance of veterans' contributions to society even after their military service, and recognized their unwavering courage and devotion. The Vice President also discussed the government's commitment to supporting veterans through initiatives such as job training, housing assistance, and healthcare benefits. She shared a personal story of a veteran who advocated for the passage of the PACT Act, which expanded healthcare and benefits for veterans and their survivors. The Vice President concluded by emphasizing the unity and shared identity of the American armed forces and the nation as a whole.